soc.message

Class SOCBuyDevCardRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • soc.message.SOCMessage
      • soc.message.SOCMessageForGame
        • soc.message.SOCBuyDevCardRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class SOCBuyDevCardRequest
extends SOCMessageForGame
    This message from client means that the client player wants to buy a development card.

    During game state PLAY1, this is a normal buy request. When sent during other game states, and other players' turns, this is a request to start the 6-player Special Building Phase.

    If the player can buy a card, the server responds with:

    • Announce game data to entire game:
      • Resource cost paid: SOCPlayerElements (gaName, playerNumber, SOCPlayerElement.LOSE, SOCDevCard.COST)
      • New remaining card count: SOCGameElements (gaName, SOCGameElements.GEType.DEV_CARD_COUNT, remainingUnboughtCount)
    • Action announcement/display:
      • Detail to the client: DEVCARDACTION(SOCDevCardAction.DRAW, cardTypeConstant)
      • To all other players: DEVCARDACTION(SOCDevCardAction.DRAW, SOCDevCardConstants.UNKNOWN)
        Sends actual card type if game option "PLAY_FO" or "PLAY_VPO" is set.
      • Action announcement to entire game: SOCSimpleAction (gaName, playerNumber, SOCSimpleAction.DEVCARD_BOUGHT, remainingUnboughtCount, 0)
      • New gameState, to entire game: SOCGameState. Usually unchanged; sent in case buying the card ended the game or otherwise changed its state. This is sent via SOCGameHandler.sendGameState(soc.game.SOCGame), which may also send other messages depending on the gameState.
    If there are no cards remaining to buy, or player doesn't have enough resources, isn't currently their turn, or the player otherwise can't buy a card right now, the server will send them a text response denying the buy. Instead of that text, robot clients will be sent a CANCELBUILDREQUEST(-2) message (-2 == soc.robot.SOCPossiblePiece.CARD).

    Before v2.0.00 this class was SOCBuyCardRequest.

    Robert S Thomas

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Description copied from class: SOCMessage
        Simple human-readable delimited representation, used for debug purposes: SOCPutPiece:game=test5|playerNumber=3|pieceType=0|coord=40a
        Could also be used by a SOCServer.recordGameEvent(String, SOCMessage) implementation.

        Within this representation, message parameters should be in same order used by SOCMessage.toCmd() and parseDataStr(..). Should be parseable by SOCMessage.parseMsgStr(String) which calls SOCMessage.stripAttribNames(String), which your class can override if needed.

        toString in class SOCMessageForGame

        a human readable form of the message
